newsitem.title: USA: U.S. jet fuel soars with NYMEX, but talk quiet.
newsitem.headline: U.S. jet fuel soars with NYMEX, but talk quiet.

text.p: U.S. spot jet fuel prices flew up by 2.00 to nearly three cents a gallon as NYMEX heating oil futures soared on the eve of a cold front's arrival in the huge Northeastern heating oil market, traders said.
But jet fuel traders said markets were exceedingly quiet and differentials a touch notional as a result.

One prompt deal for airline-quality 54-grade material closed at about 0.65 cent under December NYMEX, while in New York Harbor, offers shot up to 2.50 cents over, though the presence of any buyers could not be ascertained, traders said.
